<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Volunteer</title>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Lora:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <link href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0/css/all.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">
  <script>
    function toggleSewingQuestions(value) {
        const sewingQuestions = document.querySelector('.sewing-questions');
        if (value === "sewing") {
            sewingQuestions.style.display = 'block';
        } else {
            sewingQuestions.style.display = 'none';
        }
    }
</script>
</head>
<body>
        <!-- Nav Bar -->
        <%- include("partials/navbar") %>

        <!-- Main Content -->
<div class="main-content">
  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-header">Schedule Your Own Event</div>
    <div class="card-content">
      <p>Turtle Shelter Project vests are the perfect service project/volunteer activity for groups of all sizes and types.  
        From an individual or family to hundreds of participants at corporate events or conferences, participants will be part of 
        making vests to help save the lives of people in need. It takes 9 volunteers hours to make a vest, so we need your help!</p>

        <p>We can plan your event for the skill levels of your volunteers, and when we say that EVERY person can help, we mean it!  
        We will meet you and your volunteers at your level of skill, time and space.
        We provide all of the written and video instructions and materials - you provide the space and volunteers!  
        After your group has completed their tasks, simply send the partially completed vests back to us for expert sewing, 
        and then we will send them back to you or to a location you specify.</p>
        <p>Please fill out the form below and tell us about your event idea so that we can provide options for you and your group.</p>

        <form action="/submit" method="POST">
            <label for="first-name">First Name:</label>
            <input type="text" id="first-name" name="firstName" required>
            <br>
            <label for="last-name">Last Name:</label>
            <input type="text" id="last-name" name="lastName" required>
            <br>
            <label for="email">Email:</label>
            <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>
            <br>
            <label for="phone-number">Phone Number:</label>
            <input type="tel" id="phone-number" name="phoneNumber" required>
            <br>
            <label for="organization">Organization:</label>
            <input type="text" id="organization" name="organization">
            <br>
            <label for="event-date">Date of Event:</label>
            <input type="date" id="event-date" name="eventDate" required>
            <br>
            <label for="event-location">Location of Event:</label>
            <input type="text" id="street-address" name="streetAddress" placeholder="Street Address" required>
            <input type="text" id="city" name="city" placeholder="City" required>
            <input type="text" id="state" name="state" placeholder="State" required>
            <br>
            <label for="expected-people">How many people do you expect to show up?</label>
            <input type="number" id="expected-people" name="expectedPeople" min="1" required>
            <br>
            <label for="project-type">Sewing or Non-Sewing Project:</label>
            <select id="project-type" name="projectType" onchange="toggleSewingQuestions(this.value)" required>
                <option value="">-- Select --</option>
                <option value="sewing">Sewing</option>
                <option value="non-sewing">Non-Sewing</option>
            </select>
    
            <div class="sewing-questions">
                <h3>Sewing Project Details</h3>
                <label for="basic-sewing-skills">How many of said people have basic sewing skills?</label>
                <input type="number" id="basic-sewing-skills" name="basicSewingSkills" min="0">
    
                <label for="advanced-sewing-skills">How many of said people have advanced sewing skills?</label>
                <input type="number" id="advanced-sewing-skills" name="advancedSewingSkills" min="0">
    
                <label for="sewing-machines">How many sewing machines can you bring?</label>
                <input type="number" id="sewing-machines" name="sewingMachines" min="0">
    
                <label for="sergers">How many sergers can you bring?</label>
                <input type="number" id="sergers" name="sergers" min="0">
            </div>
    
            <button type="submit" style="margin-top: 20px;">Submit</button>
        </form>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-header">Volunteer From Home</div>
    <div class="card-content">
      <p>You can do some of the sewing or other steps of the production process at home! 
        Indicate in the form below what you would like to do. Please include your sewing skill level:</p>
        <p>No sewing: can cut, pin and mark vest components</p>
        <p>Beginning sewing: just learning to use a sewing machine</p>
        <p>Basic sewing: can sew a straight stitch</p>
        <p>Advanced sewing: can handle challenging sewing tasks.</p>
        <form action="/submit" method="POST">
          <label for="first-name">First Name:</label>
          <input type="text" id="first-name" name="firstName" required>
          <br>
          <label for="last-name">Last Name:</label>
          <input type="text" id="last-name" name="lastName" required>
          <br>
          <label for="email">Email:</label>
          <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>
          <br>
          <label for="phone-number">Phone Number:</label>
          <input type="tel" id="phone-number" name="phoneNumber" required>
          <br>
          <label for="home-address">Home Address:</label>
          <input type="text" id="street-address" name="streetAddress" placeholder="Street Address" required>
          <input type="text" id="city" name="city" placeholder="City" required>
          <input type="text" id="state" name="state" placeholder="State" required>
          <br>
          <label for="sewing-skill-level">Sewing Skill Level:</label>
          <select id="sewing-skill-level" name="sewingSkillLevel" required>
              <option value="">-- Select --</option>
              <option value="no-sewing">No Sewing</option>
              <option value="beginning-sewing">Beginning Sewing</option>
              <option value="basic-sewing">Basic Sewing</option>
              <option value="advanced-sewing">Advanced Sewing</option>
          </select>
  
          <button type="submit" style="margin-top: 20px;">Submit</button>
      </form>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-header">Become a Long-Term Volunteer</div>
    <div class="card-content">
      <p>Info about what long term volunteers do</p>

        <form action="/submit" method="POST">
            <label for="first-name">First Name:</label>
            <input type="text" id="first-name" name="firstName" required>
            <br>
            <label for="last-name">Last Name:</label>
            <input type="text" id="last-name" name="lastName" required>
            <br>
            <label for="email">Email:</label>
            <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>
            <br>
            <label for="phone-number">Phone Number:</label>
            <input type="tel" id="phone-number" name="phoneNumber" required>
            <br>
    
            <button type="submit" style="margin-top: 20px;">Submit</button>
        </form>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

  <script>
    document.querySelectorAll('.card-header').forEach(header => {
      header.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const card = header.parentElement;
        card.classList.toggle('open');
      });
    });
  </script>

      <!-- Footer -->
      <%- include("partials/footer") %>
</body>
</html>
